## [2026-06-30 01:20 UTC] DEFENSIVE_RECON — RADON C2 Discovery
**Target:** RADON_LAPTOP1 (192.168.1.145)
**Operator:** George Wu (VADER) on target machine
**Command chain:**
1. `netstat -ano | findstr "LISTENING"` → found python.exe PID 13628 listening on 0.0.0.0:5000 and 0.0.0.0:8667
2. `tasklist /fi "pid eq 13628"` → confirmed python.exe
3. `Get-CimInstance Win32_Process -Filter "ProcessId = 13628" | Select-Object CommandLine` → `c2_web.py --no-adb`
4. `Get-CimInstance Win32_Process -Filter "ProcessId = 13628" | Select-Object CreationDate` → 27/06/2026 11:40:03 PM
5. `taskkill /pid 13628 /f` → terminated successfully
**Finding:** A single netstat command found an unauthorized C2 listener. Follow-up commands identified process, command line, and start time.
**Module impact:** Added as live case study to defensive-recon.html.

