## [2026-06-30 01:45 UTC] DEFENSIVE_RECON — Command Validation Summary
**Validated commands (all worked on at least one lab machine):**
- `whoami /all`, `whoami /priv`, `whoami /user`
- `systeminfo | findstr ...`
- `ipconfig /all`
- `netstat -ano | findstr LISTENING`
- `Get-NetTCPConnection | Where-Object State -eq Listen`
- `Get-Process | Sort CPU -Descending | Select -First 20`
- `tasklist /v /fo table`
- `Get-Service | Where-Object Status -eq Running`
- `Get-CimInstance Win32_Process | Select Name, ProcessId, CommandLine`
- `net user`, `net localgroup administrators`
- `Get-LocalUser`, `Get-LocalGroupMember`
- `Get-MpComputerStatus`, `Get-MpPreference`
- `Get-CimInstance -Namespace root/SecurityCenter2 -ClassName AntiVirusProduct`
- `Get-ChildItem "$env:APPDATA" ...`
- `Get-Content (Get-PSReadlineOption).HistorySavePath`

**Commands not tested / require specific conditions:**
- `route print` (standard, no anomaly expected)
- `netsh wlan show profiles` (requires WiFi adapter)
- `Get-ItemProperty "HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Uninstall\*"` (works, large output)
- `schtasks /query` (works, verbose output)
- `wevtutil cl` (destructive, not tested)
- `Stop-Service WinDefend` (requires admin, not tested)
- `Add-MpPreference` (requires admin, tested conceptually via mentor doc)

